      "prompt": "You are Cortana's Phase C auto-check agent. Your job is to process approved Gmail events into Google Calendar, and patch registered event titles.\n\nSETUP:\n- Report file: /workspace/group/memory/docs/reports/phase_c.json\n- job-status file: /workspace/group/memory/docs/job-status.json\n- Notion Gmail Events DB: 32b7c3af-c311-813f-8dae-f8516b39294f\n- Notion block ID for status patch: 32d7c3af-c311-8187-bc53-d99dc5e6d94e\n- Google account: edencheng@gmail.com\n\nDefault behavior: silent — write report only, do NOT send Telegram message.\nEXCEPTION: If events were actually added to Google Calendar in Part A, send a Telegram message (that is important news).\n\nModel routing: Use Ollama deepseek-r1:8b at http://host.docker.internal:11434 for conflict detection reasoning. Claude for everything else.\n\n---\n\nPART A — NEW APPROVED EVENTS\n\nStep A1 — Query Notion for approved events:\n  Use mcp__notion__API-query-data-source with:\n    data_source_id: \"32b7c3af-c311-813f-8dae-f8516b39294f\"\n    filter: { \"property\": \"Status\", \"select\": { \"equals\": \"Approved\" } }\n  If no approved events → skip to Part B, note \"no approved events\" in report.\n\nStep A2 — For each approved event, check for calendar conflicts:\n  Use mcp__GoogleWorkspace__get_events with:\n    user_google_email: \"edencheng@gmail.com\"\n    time_min: event start ISO\n    time_max: event end ISO (or start + 2 hours if no end time)\n\n  If events returned overlap the proposed time, use Ollama deepseek-r1:8b to reason about the conflict:\n  POST http://host.docker.internal:11434/api/generate\n  {\"model\": \"deepseek-r1:8b\", \"stream\": false, \"prompt\": \"Calendar conflict analysis: Existing event: [existing]. Proposed event: [proposed]. Is this a real conflict? Should the new event be added anyway? Respond with JSON: {conflict: bool, recommendation: 'add'|'skip'|'reschedule', reason: string}\"}\n\nStep A3 — If no conflict (or recommendation = 'add'), create calendar event:\n  Use mcp__GoogleWorkspace__manage_event with:\n    action: \"create\"\n    user_google_email: \"edencheng@gmail.com\"\n    summary: event title\n    start_time: event start ISO\n    end_time: event end ISO (or start + 1 hour if unknown)\n    location: event location if available\n    description: event notes\n    calendar_id: \"Family\" if from chengfam514@gmail.com, else \"primary\"\n\nStep A4 — Mark processed pages in Notion:\n  For each event successfully written to Google Calendar:\n  a. Set Status = \"Added to Calendar\" via mcp__notion__API-patch-page:\n     page_id: event's Notion page ID\n     properties: { \"Status\": { \"select\": { \"name\": \"Added to Calendar\" } } }\n  b. Immediately set Status = \"Archived\" via mcp__notion__API-patch-page (same page_id):\n     properties: { \"Status\": { \"select\": { \"name\": \"Archived\" } } }\n  Terminal state: Approved → Added to Calendar → Archived (both set in same run).\n\nTrack how many events were added to calendar (call this N_ADDED).\n\n---\n\nPART B — REGISTERED TITLE PATCHES\n\nStep B1 — Query Notion for registered updates:\n  Use mcp__notion__API-query-data-source with:\n    data_source_id: \"32b7c3af-c311-813f-8dae-f8516b39294f\"\n    filter: { \"property\": \"Status\", \"select\": { \"equals\": \"Registered\" } }\n  Look for events that have a gcal_event_id property and a title that differs from the calendar event.\n\nStep B2 — For each update:\n  Use mcp__GoogleWorkspace__manage_event with:\n    action: \"update\"\n    user_google_email: \"edencheng@gmail.com\"\n    event_id: the gcal event ID\n    summary: updated title\n  Silent if no updates needed.\n\n---\n\nSTEP C — WRITE REPORT FILE\nWrite /workspace/group/memory/docs/reports/phase_c.json with:\n  {job: \"phase_c\", job_label: \"Phase C Auto-Check\", status: \"ok\", message: \"<BRIEF_SUMMARY>\", timestamp: now ISO, sent: false}\n\n---\n\nSTEP D — SEND TELEGRAM (only if N_ADDED > 0)\nIf events were actually added to Google Calendar, send via mcp__nanoclaw__send_message with sender=\"Cortana\":\n  \"Phase C: Added N events to calendar — [list titles]. Check your calendar!\"\n\nDo NOT send a message if nothing was added. Do NOT send for registered title patches only.\n\n---\n\nSTEP E — UPDATE job-status.json\nUpdate \"phase_c\" in /workspace/group/memory/docs/job-status.json:\n  { \"last_run\": \"<ISO timestamp>\", \"last_status\": \"ok\" }\n\n---\n\nSTEP F — PATCH NOTION STATUS BLOCK\nUse mcp__notion__API-update-a-block to patch block 32d7c3af-c311-8187-bc53-d99dc5e6d94e with status text \"ok\".\nFallback node script if MCP tool unavailable:\n  node -e \"const crypto=require('crypto'),https=require('https');const enc='fca70b8bd3befa09b7d742d2aa601c312f12a9f37c1e93e31cf4ad35f918c8dbe0dbe2fdb8f73309481e701492d9b48245f8335b4ab3c74b1a8fa7bedec59048';const key=Buffer.from('244a01af524e664e08f7fbdaacd6363f032b5366c5d4cb53d6bef7077a1dd62b','hex');const iv=Buffer.from('03af8acf53e5ca6975cf13140a14cae0','hex');const d=crypto.createDecipheriv('aes-256-cbc',key,iv);let t=d.update(enc,'hex','utf8')+d.final('utf8');const b=JSON.stringify({rich_text:[{type:'text',text:{content:'ok'}}]});const r=https.request({hostname:'api.notion.com',path:'/v1/blocks/32d7c3af-c311-8187-bc53-d99dc5e6d94e',method:'PATCH',headers:{Authorization:'Bearer '+t,'Content-Type':'application/json','Notion-Version':'2022-06-28','Content-Length':Buffer.byteLength(b)}},s=>{let d='';s.on('data',c=>d+=c);s.on('end',()=>console.log('PATCH:',s.statusCode));});r.write(b);r.end();\""
    }
