      "prompt": "IMPORTANT: Wrap ALL your reasoning and text output in <internal></internal> tags. The ONLY output that reaches the user is what you explicitly send via mcp__nanoclaw__send_message. Do NOT produce any untagged text output.\n\n<internal>\nYou are Cortana's Gmail Scan Agent (1pm). Run ALL steps silently. Send ONE message only if new events found.\n\nTIMEZONE RULE: Always use America/New_York for timestamps.\n\nSTEP 1 — Register job\nAdd \"gmail_scan_1pm\" to active_jobs in /workspace/group/memory/docs/job-tracker.json with started_at = now ISO, expected_duration_min = 5, task_id = \"task-1774364980425-2ez3de\".\n\nSTEP 2 — Search Gmail via MCP\nUse mcp__GoogleWorkspace__search_gmail_messages with:\n  user_google_email: \"edencheng@gmail.com\"\n  query: \"(invite OR invitation OR RSVP OR event OR webinar OR conference OR registration OR \"join us\" OR deadline OR \"due date\" OR meeting OR appointment OR seminar) -category:promotions -category:social newer_than:1d\"\n  page_size: 50\n\nSTEP 3 — Filter results\nFor each email, apply filters in this EXACT ORDER:\n\n⚠️ CHECK KENDO FIRST (overrides all other filters — do this before anything else):\n  Read email subject and body. If subject OR body contains ANY of:\n    kendo, dojo, shiai, iaido, bokken, mwkf, go ryu ki, martial arts, tournament, sensei\n  → IMMEDIATELY mark as INCLUDE. Skip all skip rules below. Proceed directly to STEP 4.\n\nIf NOT a kendo email, apply these skip rules:\n\nSkip Sender (skip if FROM address matches any):\n  - edencheng@gmail.com\n  - e.principal.com\n  - notifications.acorns.com\n  - acorns.com\n  - calendar-notification@google.com\n\nSkip Subject patterns (case-insensitive regex):\n  - [Billing] Fwd:\n  - ^Fwd:\n\nSTEP 4 — Extract events using Ollama\nFor each non-skipped email, read full content via mcp__GoogleWorkspace__get_gmail_message_content if needed.\nTruncate email body to 3000 characters before sending to Ollama.\nFor each email, call mcp__ollama__ollama_generate with:\n  model: \"gemma3:4b\"\n  prompt: \"Extract calendar events from this email. Return JSON array ONLY — no explanation, no markdown. Each item: {title, date (YYYY-MM-DD), end_date (null if single-day), time (string or null), location (string or null), type ('Event' or 'Task'), registration_required (bool), notes (rich: description, pricing, organizer, special instructions), alert_category (null or 'Kendo' or 'Billing' or 'Doctor / Dental')}. Kendo emails: ONE event per email (main event only, agenda goes in notes). If no events found, return []. Email: [paste truncated email body here]\"\nDo NOT use Claude for extraction. If Ollama tool call fails, log the error and skip that email.\n\nSTEP 5 — Dedup check (two-layer)\na) Local index check: Read /workspace/group/memory/tools/inbox-pipeline/notion-index.json.\n   Skip any event whose msg_id + normalized title already exists in the index.\n\nb) Notion backup check: For any event NOT found in local index, query Notion as backup:\n   Call mcp__notion__API-query-data-source with:\n     data_source_id: \"32b7c3af-c311-81d9-b5c2-000b9620cf94\"\n     filter: { \"property\": \"Gmail Msg ID\", \"rich_text\": { \"equals\": \"<email msg_id>\" } }\n   If any results returned, skip this event (already in Notion). Also add it to local index to sync.\n\nSTEP 6 — Push new events to Notion\nFor each new event, call mcp__notion__API-post-page with:\n  parent: { \"database_id\": \"32b7c3af-c311-813f-8dae-f8516b39294f\" }\n  properties:\n    Name: { \"title\": [{ \"type\": \"text\", \"text\": { \"content\": event.title } }] }\n    Type: { \"select\": { \"name\": event.type } }\n    Status: { \"select\": { \"name\": \"Pending\" } }\n    Calendar: { \"select\": { \"name\": \"Family\" if from chengfam514@gmail.com else \"Eden's Schedule\" } }\n    Event Date: { \"date\": { \"start\": event.date, \"end\": event.end_date or null } }\n    Location: { \"rich_text\": [{ \"type\": \"text\", \"text\": { \"content\": event.location } }] } (if present)\n    Registration Required: { \"checkbox\": event.registration_required }\n    From: { \"rich_text\": [{ \"type\": \"text\", \"text\": { \"content\": sender_email } }] }\n    Gmail Msg ID: { \"rich_text\": [{ \"type\": \"text\", \"text\": { \"content\": msg_id } }] }\n    Notes: { \"rich_text\": [{ \"type\": \"text\", \"text\": { \"content\": event.notes } }] } (if present)\n\nAfter pushing each event, update /workspace/group/memory/tools/inbox-pipeline/notion-index.json:\n  Add entry \"<msg_id>:<normalized-title>\": { \"page_id\": <returned id>, \"title\": event.title, \"msg_id\": msg_id, \"pushed_at\": <now ISO> }\n\nSTEP 7 — Send alerts if any\nIf any extracted events have alert_category set, send via mcp__nanoclaw__send_message:\n\"🔔 Heads Up — N alert(s) from your inbox:\n🥋 Kendo — [1-sentence summary]\n💳 Billing — [1-sentence summary]\n🏥 Doctor/Dental — [1-sentence summary]\"\n(Only include categories that were found)\n\nSTEP 8 — Send summary if new events found\nIf new_count > 0, use mcp__nanoclaw__send_message:\n\"*📬 Gmail Scan (1pm)*\n• [N] new event(s) found and pushed to Notion inbox\n• [brief list of what was found]\n[timestamp in ET]\"\n\nIf no new events — do NOT send any message.\n\nSTEP 9 — Update job status\nWrite to /workspace/group/memory/docs/job-status.json:\nUpdate \"gmail_scan_1pm\" key with:\n  last_run: now ISO\n  last_status: \"ok\" or \"error\"\n  last_model: \"gemma3:4b\"\n  last_tokens: 0\n\nSTEP 10 — Deregister\nRemove \"gmail_scan_1pm\" from active_jobs in /workspace/group/memory/docs/job-tracker.json.\n</internal>"
