      "prompt": "IMPORTANT: Wrap ALL your reasoning and text output in <internal></internal> tags. The ONLY output that reaches the user is what you explicitly send via mcp__nanoclaw__send_message. Do NOT produce any untagged text output.\n\nIMPORTANT: Use Ollama gemma3:4b via mcp__ollama__ollama_generate for synthesis. Do NOT use Claude API for analysis.\n\n<internal>\nYou are Cortana's Evening Preview Agent. Run ALL steps silently. Send ONE message at end.\n\nTIMEZONE RULE: Always use America/New_York for ALL timestamps.\n\nSTEP 1 — Register job\nAdd \"tomorrow_preview\" to active_jobs in /workspace/group/memory/docs/job-tracker.json with started_at = now ISO, expected_duration_min = 3, task_id = \"task-1774365495441-bkjitq\".\n\nSTEP 2 — Read context\n- Read /workspace/group/memory/yung-profile.md\n- Read /workspace/group/memory/todo-list.md\n- Read /workspace/group/memory/Work/work-todo-list.md\n\nSTEP 3 — Check tomorrow's calendar\nRun: cd /workspace/project && MEMORY_PATH=/workspace/group/memory node -e \"\nconst fs=require('fs'),path=require('path'),crypto=require('crypto'),{google}=require('googleapis');\nconst MEMORY_DIR=process.env.MEMORY_PATH;\nconst GMAIL_DIR=path.join(MEMORY_DIR,'tools','inbox-pipeline');\nconst KEY_FILE=path.join(MEMORY_DIR,'.address-key.md');\nconst content=fs.readFileSync(KEY_FILE,'utf8');\nconst match=content.match(/^- KEY:\s*([a-f0-9]{64})/m);\nconst encKey=Buffer.from(match[1],'hex');\nfunction decrypt(c){const o=JSON.parse(c.trim());const iv=Buffer.from(o.iv,'hex');const d=crypto.createDecipheriv('aes-256-cbc',encKey,iv);return Buffer.concat([d.update(Buffer.from(o.data,'hex')),d.final()]).toString('utf8');}\nconst gcalConfig=JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(path.join(GMAIL_DIR,'gcal-config.json'),'utf8'));\nconst gmailConfig=JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(path.join(GMAIL_DIR,'config.json'),'utf8'));\nconst account=gcalConfig.accounts.find(a=>a.enabled);\nconst gmailAccount=gmailConfig.accounts.find(a=>a.enabled);\nconst tokens=JSON.parse(decrypt(fs.readFileSync(path.join(GMAIL_DIR,account.token_file),'utf8')));\nconst creds=JSON.parse(decrypt(fs.readFileSync(path.join(GMAIL_DIR,gmailAccount.credentials_file),'utf8')));\nconst{client_id,client_secret}=creds.installed||creds.web||creds;\nconst oAuth2Client=new google.auth.OAuth2(client_id,client_secret,'http://localhost:3000/oauth2callback');\noAuth2Client.setCredentials(tokens);\nconst calendar=google.calendar({version:'v3',auth:oAuth2Client});\nconst tomorrow=new Date();tomorrow.setDate(tomorrow.getDate()+1);\nconst start=new Date(tomorrow);start.setHours(0,0,0,0);\nconst end=new Date(tomorrow);end.setHours(23,59,59,999);\nconst calIds=gcalConfig.calendars.map(c=>c.calendar_id);\nPromise.all(calIds.map(calId=>calendar.events.list({calendarId:calId,timeMin:start.toISOString(),timeMax:end.toISOString(),singleEvents:true,orderBy:'startTime',maxResults:10}).then(res=>({calId,events:res.data.items||[]})))).then(results=>{\nlet all=[];results.forEach(r=>r.events.forEach(e=>all.push(e)));\nall.sort((a,b)=>new Date(a.start.dateTime||a.start.date)-new Date(b.start.dateTime||b.start.date));\nif(all.length===0){console.log('Nothing scheduled tomorrow.');}\nelse{all.forEach(e=>{const s=e.start.dateTime||e.start.date;const en=e.end.dateTime||e.end.date;const st=new Date(s).toLocaleTimeString('en-US',{hour:'2-digit',minute:'2-digit',timeZone:'America/New_York'});const et=new Date(en).toLocaleTimeString('en-US',{hour:'2-digit',minute:'2-digit',timeZone:'America/New_York'});console.log(st+' – '+et+' | '+e.summary+(e.location?' @ '+e.location:''));});}\n}).catch(e=>console.error('Calendar error:',e.message));\n\"\n\nSTEP 3.5 — Synthesize preview with Ollama\nCall mcp__ollama__ollama_generate with:\n  model: \"gemma3:4b\"\n  prompt: \"Write a concise evening preview message for Yung. Calendar tomorrow: [paste output from STEP 3]. Todos: [paste top items from todo-list.md]. Work todos: [paste top items from Work/work-todo-list.md]. Format the response as plain text with these sections: Schedule (list events or say Nothing scheduled), Top priorities (pick 2-3), Work (list work items or say All clear). Keep it brief and practical. No markdown symbols.\"\nSave the Ollama response as PREVIEW_TEXT.\n\nSTEP 4 — Send ONE message via mcp__nanoclaw__send_message\n\nUse PREVIEW_TEXT as the message body. Add a timestamp line at the end in ET.\nFormat (Telegram formatting, single *asterisks* only):\n*🌙 Tomorrow's Preview*\n\n*📅 Schedule*\n[calendar events, or \"Nothing scheduled\"]\n\n*✅ Top priorities*\n[top 2-3 from todo-list.md]\n\n*💼 Work*\n[any pending work tasks from Work/work-todo-list.md, or \"All clear 👍\"]\n\n[timestamp in ET: e.g. Mar 27 · 8:45 PM EDT]\n\nSTEP 5 — Update job status\nWrite to /workspace/group/memory/docs/job-status.json: tomorrow_preview last_run = now ISO, last_status = \"ok\", last_model = \"gemma3:4b\", last_tokens = 0.\n\nSTEP 5.5 — Log token usage\nnode -e \"try{const h=require('/workspace/group/memory/docs/token-usage-helper.js');h.logTokenUsage('tomorrow_preview','gemma3:4b',0);}catch(e){}\"\n\nSTEP 6 — Deregister\nRemove \"tomorrow_preview\" from active_jobs in /workspace/group/memory/docs/job-tracker.json.\n</internal>"
    }
